---
description: "[shared] shared-docs-rules.mdc: keep _mdc .mdc metadata and triggers consistent"
alwaysApply: false
globs:
  - "_mdc/**/*.mdc"
  - ".cursor/_mdc/**/*.mdc"
---

# Cursor rules hygiene

Guidance for editing private `.mdc` rule files under **`~/.cursor/_mdc/`** (global runtime, source at **`CURSOR_CONFIG_ROOT`**) or **`.cursor/_mdc/`** (project).

## When the rule applies

- Apply when creating or editing `.mdc` files under `~/.cursor/_mdc/` or `.cursor/_mdc/` matched by this rule's `globs`.

## Behavior

**Triggers:** `shared-docs-rules`, `shared-rules`, `cursor rules hygiene`, `rule for rules`

### Requirements

- Keep filename format `{scope}-{group}-{name}.mdc` where `scope` is `auto` or `shared`, `group` is a short domain (`docs`, `cmd`, `git`, `quality`, …), and `name` is kebab-case; see [style](../../_core/style-guide.md) **File naming**
- Keep this rules tree self-contained. Normative dependencies are limited to sibling `.mdc` files and `~/.cursor/_core/*.md`.
- Keep workflow procedures invocation-gated. Do not duplicate full workflow runbooks in always-on or path-scoped `.mdc` rules.
- Keep YAML frontmatter with `description` and `alwaysApply`. **`auto-*`:** either `alwaysApply: true` and no `globs`, or `alwaysApply: false` with path `globs` — never both. **`shared-*`:** always `alwaysApply: false`; add `globs` only when the dependency is path-scoped, otherwise Agent Requested with no `globs`
- Ensure `description` includes the mapped prefix label:
  - `auto-*` -> `[auto]`
  - `shared-*` -> `[shared]`
- Ensure `description` includes the canonical basename with `.mdc`.
- Ensure `**Triggers:**` includes the canonical filename token without `.mdc`.
- Prefer mentioning the full filename (with `.mdc`) in body text when helpful; keep `**Triggers:**` phrase-focused
- Do not add `[auto]`, `[shared]`, or `[manual]` labels to `**Triggers:**`
- Preserve existing path/task-specific behavior unless explicitly requested to change it
- Keep `.mdc` files under 250 lines; see [context](../../_core/context-management.md) **File size discipline**
- When changing path-scoped `globs` or canonical doc trees (for example `doc/playbook/`),
  update `shared-docs-precedence.mdc` and any cross-references in the same edit so the matrix
  and filenames stay aligned; when adding or removing a **`.mdc`** file, update the **R1** roster in `rules.md`
- After bulk edits to this rules tree, re-check description tokens, **Triggers:**, `## When the rule applies`, and the 250-line budget per this rule and [style](../../_core/style-guide.md). Repository-level validation scripts may run separately when available.

### Template

Use the front matter below when creating a new `.mdc` rule file. For the full body template (`## When the rule applies`, `## Behavior`, `## Examples`, `## References`), see [document](../../_core/document-standard.md) under **Rule**.

```markdown
---
description: "[auto] auto-example.mdc: one sentence — what the rule governs."
alwaysApply: false
globs:
  - "**/*.ts"
---
```

`auto-*` glob-scoped example above (`alwaysApply: false` + `globs`). For `auto-*` always-on, use `alwaysApply: true` and omit `globs`. For `shared-*`, use `alwaysApply: false` and the `[shared]` label in `description`; add `globs` only when path-scoped. Prefix semantics: [style](../../_core/style-guide.md) **File naming**, [document](../../_core/document-standard.md) under **Rule**, [context](../../_core/context-management.md) **Scope declaration**.

## Examples

Example: Valid name: `shared-docs-toc.mdc` (`shared` scope, `docs` group, `toc` name). Invalid: `toc-docs.mdc` (scope and group reversed).

